snippet.textDisplay:
I... I am speechless. I have been making my bestie listen to this song again and again, and I myself am constantly having it being played back in my mind throughout the day even when it is not playing in real. I feel so so connected to it, and that is even regardless of the fact that I am a Punjabi. The way this song portrays the extra platonic nature of Punjabis is crazy on a different level. This is one of those songs with which I will be dying with, keeping them in my playlist till my last breath. The most awesome of a song coupled with my favourite artist, Faris Shafi, being the artist of it is... I love you, Xulfi bhai. I love you, Faris! I love you, Umair! I love Gharvi group. And I love each and every artist played who has had a role in the making of this song, be it the artists with the instruments, the crew who set the stage, the people who provided additional help in the making of the song. EVERYONE!

I am not well-versed with music as in its technical aspects, but I have this constant urge to listen to music all the time, whether I understand the lyrics or not and just sing along with it. And I swear to God, the most heart-touching or addicted songs I have ever listened have come out of Coke Studio, especially from S14 and S15.

Thanks a lot, Xulfi bhai, for creating soul-feeding music.

Allah SwT apko khair abaad rakhey, or apko hamesha khush rakhey.

Sincerely,
Your fan!
